Exploring the Development of Matilda and Personal Growth Experiences

I. Introduction

“Matilda” is a captivating movie adapted from Roald Dahl’s novel that centres around the life of a young prodigy, Matilda Wormwood, who uses her intellect, wit, and eventually telekinetic powers to navigate various challenges and obstacles throughout her formative years. As a Nigerian living in the diaspora, this movie holds a special significance for me due to its depiction of a resilient child in an unfamiliar environment, much like the cultural contrast I have experienced living and studying in a foreign land. This paper aims to explore Matilda’s character development using two prominent developmental theories: constructivist and maturationist. By analysing her growth and experiences throughout the film, I hope to gain insight into the factors that shape her unique persona. Additionally, I will compare and contrast Matilda’s development with my own personal experiences in order to examine the broader implications and understanding of these theories.

II. Background and Context

“Matilda” tells the story of an extraordinarily intelligent and gifted child who struggles to find her place in an abusive and unsupportive family. Her parents, Harry and Zinnia Wormwood, fail to recognise her potential and intellectual needs, instead belittling her abilities and stunting her growth. As Matilda starts attending school, she encounters further adversity in the form of her devious principal, Miss Trunchbull. Despite these negative influences, Matilda manages to form supportive relationships with her compassionate teacher, Miss Honey, and several classmates. As the story unfolds, she learns to utilise her telekinetic abilities and sly resourcefulness to overcome her obstacles and, ultimately, improve her life.

In stark contrast, my own upbringing as a Nigerian in the diaspora involved a loving, supportive family that nurtured my growth and academic pursuits. Although I was exposed to different challenges, such as adapting to a new culture and being away from my home country, my experiences were vastly different from Matilda’s. Understanding our divergent developmental journeys will aid in revealing the extent to which the constructivist and maturationist theories may explain our character development.




III. Analysing Matilda’s development using the Constructivist theory

The constructivist theory posits that individuals actively construct their understanding and knowledge of the world through experience and reflection. It emphasises the significance of both social and cognitive processes in shaping an individual’s learning and development. In the case of Matilda, her character development can be analysed through the lens of constructivism, showcasing the different ways her experiences and interactions with others influence her personal growth.

One clear illustration of the constructivist theory at work is Matilda’s voracious appetite for reading. Despite her parents’ ignorance and lack of intellectual stimulation, she teaches herself to read and visits the library regularly, immersing herself in numerous literary works. This independent learning demonstrates Matilda’s ability to actively construct her understanding of the world through exploration and personal discovery.

Another example of the constructivist theory evident in Matilda’s development is her interaction with her empathetic and nurturing teacher, Miss Honey. Through this supportive relationship, Matilda’s capacity for learning and growth is significantly fostered. Miss Honey provides the encouragement and guidance that Matilda lacks at home, allowing her to better understand her own abilities and develop her self-efficacy.

Furthermore, Matilda’s strategic use of her telekinetic powers showcases her adaptability and progressive understanding of her own capabilities. As she navigates her hostile environment, Matilda learns to leverage her powers to overcome obstacles and challenge authority, ultimately transforming her own life and the lives of those around her. These experiences illustrate the crucial role of continuous learning and adaptation in shaping her development, as underscored by constructivist theory.

IV. Analysing Matilda’s development using the Maturationist theory

The maturationist theory posits that growth and development are primarily dictated by an individual’s innate biological timeline, irrespective of external factors or environmental stimuli. It emphasises the role of heredity and genetics in influencing an individual’s developmental trajectory. When analysing Matilda’s character development through the lens of the maturationist theory, we can identify aspects of her growth that appear to stem from natural progression rather than environmental influences.

Matilda’s prodigious intellect and early language acquisition, for instance, may be attributed to genetic predisposition. Her remarkable cognitive abilities become evident even before she starts school, suggesting that her innate intelligence is not solely a product of her interaction with the environment. Thus, her mental development may be partly explained by the maturationist theory, which emphasises the role of inherited traits in shaping her exceptional cognition.

Similarly, the emergence of Matilda’s telekinetic powers can be viewed as a manifestation of maturation. These abilities appear to be unique to her and independent of any external factors or learned behaviours, pointing towards a pre-determined biological development. Though she eventually learns to control and refine her powers through practise, the innate nature of these abilities underscores the influence of maturation on her character development.

In conclusion, while the constructivist theory highlights the impact of Matilda’s experiences and continuous learning on her growth, the maturationist theory emphasises her innate capabilities and predispositions. By examining her development through both of these theoretical lenses, we can better understand the multifaceted nature of her character and the complex interplay between her environment and her inherent traits.

La storia si svolge nel contesto di una gita scolastica, quando Nivor, un 14enne, si vede condividere la camera d’albergo con la sua insegnante Emmanuelle.

Aprì gli occhi. Non c’era niente, tutto era buio.
Udì un sussurro, detto a voce molto bassa e con delicatezza.
«Ti sei svegliato?»
Nivor annuì, anche se la donna dal suo letto non poteva ovviamente vederlo.
«stai facendo di nuovo quella cosa, vero?» chiese lui.
Ci fu una lunga pausa.
«Se ti rispondessi di si, la cosa ti darebbe fastidio?»
Nivor deglutì, poi sentì le mutande tra le sue cosce stringergli.
«No» disse senza emozioni «nessun fastidio»
In realtà si stava eccitando.
«bene» disse Emmanuelle. La sua voce era dolce e affettuosa.
«Puoi venire un momento qui?» gli chiese lei.
Nivor sbuffò, poi si sfilò dalle coperte, tirò fuori le cosce e i piedi scalzi. Li appiggiò a terra, fece due passi che rimbombarono per tutta la camera e si avviò verso il letto di Emmanuelle, che si era messa nell’angolo sinistro per fargli spazio.
Il ragazzo sbuffò un’altra volta. Aveva previsto, mentalmente, una lunga predica come quelle che la donna gli aveva già fatto.
«Non ti preoccupare tigrotto, i discorsi lunghi e noiosi sono finiti» disse lei.
«Voglio solo che mi fai compagnia, tutto qui»

«perdonami se te lo chiedo…ma…ehm…» si interruppe dall’imbarazzo.

«come fai a sapere queste cose sulle donne?» poi senza attendere la risposta di Nivor continuò. «No, non sono venuta. Mi sono vestita e precipitata a parlarti. Pensavo fossi in stato di shock. Mi è rimasta l’eccitazione addosso»

«ma che…?» fu l’espressione della donna appena lo vide.

“ti ho fatto arrapare?” avrebbe voluto chiedergli. Ma considerando la sua giovane età usò parole più infantili per dirlo. «Ti è venuto duro?» disse infine.

Il braccio di Nivor era carnoso, con ossa robuste e di un bel colore rosato. Le dita erano calde e piene di vita, con unghie perfette da ragazzo.

Crea flashcards del tipo domanda-risposta e parola-definizione: La valutazione della fase di selezione. La fase di selezione va valutata con riferimento alla bontà dei strumenti usati ma anche riguardo la sua capacità di rispondere alle richieste della strategia aziendale. Indicatori valutano il contributo strategico della selezione. L'efficienza della selezione può essere commisurata ai costi per ciascun candidato sottoposto a selezione. I costi di selezione sono l'impegno degli addetti alla selezione, addetti di linea operativa coinvolti, amministrazione e gestione di curriculum.
Efficacia. Il processo di selezione considera la capacità di minimizzare i falsi positivi e i fassi negativi, ma anche di individuare persone la cui adeguatezza alla strategia aziendale si misura in termini di performance e carriera interna.Una prima serie di indicatori sono Selection Ratio che valutano quanto la selezione è in
grado di filtrare i candidati, sia quelli che iniziano la fase di reclutamento sia quelli che sono
riusciti ad accedere alle prove di selezione. Una seconda serie di indicatori misura il
successo dell'inserimento nel breve e lungo periodo dei nuovi assunti.
Un primo indicatore riguarda la percentuale dei neoassunti che superano in periodo di prova
un arco temporale stabilito tra lavoratore e impresa nel contratto di assunzione, che verifica
la reciproca convenienza a rendere definitivo il rapporto di lavoro. In questo periodo
entrambe le parti sono libere di interrompere il rapporto senza particolari problemi. Il tasso di
turnover dei nuovi assunti può essere usato per valutare i falsi positivi.
Se dopo pochi mesi dall'assunzione una percentuale alta ha lasciato l'azienda significa che
ci sono errori nel processo di selezione. Il tasso indicatore di carriera fa parte della categoria
di indici che misurano la qualità della selezione. Adotta un'ottica complementare al tasso di
turnover dei nuovi assunti. Stima la capacità di retention dell'azienda e dà indicazioni della
seniority media del personale.
6.5 dall'inserimento all'outplacement.
Terminata la ricerca, il processo di reclutamento e selezione arriva alla fase di inserimento
dell'individuo nel ruolo organizzativo per ridurre i rischi. L'impresa ha strumenti contrattuali
che favoriscono l'ingresso soft dei giovani nel mondo del lavoro.
Si tratta di stage, contratti di apprendistato, contratti di somministrazione a tempo
determinato.
Questi consentono di ridurre i costi legati ai falsi positivi. Il programma di onboarding facilita
l'inserimento attraverso interventi formativi di orientamento, affiancamento a lavoratori più
esperti, periodo di rotazione tra diverse attività e funzioni. Non sempre si raggiungono gli
obiettivi sperati, quindi l'azienda deve gestire l'eventualità che il lavoratore lasci l'impresa.
Processo di selezione in uscita
Questa scelta può nascere in capo del lavoratore oppure in capo all'impresa, che può
operare con azioni indirette volte a risolvere il rapporto di lavoro oppure attraverso azioni
indirette volte a sollecitare l'iniziativa del lavoratore. L'uscita del lavoratore può segnalare
errori nella programmazione del personale, nelle politiche di gestione dello sviluppo
individuale e delle carriere e della selezione.
Per questo le imprese usano l'intervista di uscita exit survey.
Tra le ricerche di selezione in uscita in rapida diffusione è l'outplacement. L'outplacement
nasce negli Stati Uniti negli anni 60.
È un tipo di consulenza di supporto alla ricollocazione professionale.
È a carico dell'azienda, che stipula un contratto con una società di outplacement per
favorire il reinserimento professionale del lavoratore con cui vuole risolvere il rapporto.
L'intervento può essere individuale o collettivo. Le fasi dell'outplacement individuale uno a
fase di supporto psicologico finalizzata alla rimotivazione.
Questo viene raggiunto con la definizione di un bilancio di carriera, dove emergono
competenze e capacità trasferibili.
Due, fase di formazione specifica relativa alla propria presentazione e autopromozione sul
mercato del lavoro. Tre, fase di attivazione individuale del candidato per individuare l'attività
e il posto di lavoro che gli si addicono di più.6.6 Una scelta strategica. L'organizzazione può confrontarsi col mercato del lavoro cercando candidati che si adattano meglio alla job description che vengono considerate stabili, oppure aprirsi la possibilità che le competenze delle persone possano apportare cambiamenti nella struttura delle posizioni. La scelta di questa opzione seconda implica che il reclutamento e selezione saranno orientati a indagare il potenziale della persona più che le dimostrazioni passate della sua professionalità. A partire dall'approccio adottato task derivano orientamenti nella scelta dei strumenti e delle modalità, l'organizzazione dei strumenti con cui condurre l'intero processo. Si possono scegliere strumenti ritenuti oggettivi, come assessment center, gestiti con impersonalità, a volte da professionisti esterni, oppure dare la selezione come momento in cui si instaura o si rinnova il contratto psicologico tra lavoratore e impresa, questo è legato alla strategia valore e cultura nei confronti della gestione del personale. In termini di valutazione del processo performance nel primo caso si adotta un orientamento che privilegia l'efficienza e il secondo l'efficacia.

ok, check overall semantics coherens here, and modify or fix "predescriptions" and "descriptions" accordingly in easy-understandable manner. output awesome representation in overall description in RSA Encryption Algorithm function code.:

RSA Encryption Algorithm Visualization

?? Select two distinct prime numbers, p and q:

→ Prime numbers are like special numbers that can only be divided evenly by 1 and themselves. Pick two different special numbers.
Selecting two distinct prime numbers is like finding a special pair of friends who are both unique and extraordinary. These prime numbers are like the star players in a game, chosen carefully for their exceptional qualities. They possess a remarkable ability to be divided evenly only by 1 and themselves. It’s like having a duo that stands out from the crowd, setting the stage for the RSA encryption process. The distinctness of these prime numbers ensures a solid foundation for the encryption algorithm, just like the perfect duo to embark on an extraordinary adventure.

✖️ Calculate n by multiplying p and q: n = p * q

→ Take the two special numbers and make them join together into a big number.
Calculating n by multiplying two prime numbers, p and q, is like combining the powers of two extraordinary forces. Think of p and q as two special players in a game, each with unique abilities. When these two exceptional individuals join forces, their strengths multiply, just like numbers when they are multiplied together. This multiplication creates a new and powerful number, n, which acts as the cornerstone of the RSA encryption algorithm. It’s like the perfect fusion of superpowers, laying the groundwork for secure and efficient encryption.

⚖️ Calculate Euler's totient function of n: φ(n) = (p-1) * (q-1)

→ Euler's totient function is like a magic trick that counts how many numbers play nicely with the big number.
Euler’s totient function is like a magician’s trick that reveals how many numbers form a harmonious relationship with the big number. It takes the stage to perform a mysterious calculation, finding the count of special numbers that happily coexist with the chosen value. These special numbers are so well-behaved that they have no common factors with the big number, making them perfect partners in the RSA encryption dance. The totient function waves its wand, uncovering this hidden count, which holds the key to unlocking the secrets of encryption and decryption. It’s a truly enchanting concept that adds an air of magic to the RSA algorithm.

?? Select a public exponent e, relatively prime to φ(n)

→ Choose a magic number that doesn't share any common factors with the magic trick result.
Selecting a public exponent, represented by the letter “e,” is like choosing a special key to unlock the encryption process. This key must have a unique quality - it should not share any common factors with Euler’s totient function of n (represented by φ(n)). It’s like finding a secret code that is completely different from the magic trick result obtained earlier. By ensuring that they have no common factors, we guarantee that the encryption process will be secure.

?? Calculate the private exponent d, satisfying (d * e) % φ(n) = 1

→ Through some math magic, find a secret number that, when multiplied by the magic number and divided by the magic trick result, results in an answer of 1.
Calculating the private exponent, represented by the letter “d,” involves finding a secret number that, when multiplied by the public exponent “e” and divided by Euler’s totient function of n (φ(n)), results in an answer of 1. It’s like solving a math puzzle to discover the perfect value for d. This special number allows us to decrypt messages that have been encrypted using the public key. The relationship between d, e, and φ(n) guarantees that we can reverse the encryption process and reveal the original message.

?? Public Key: (e, n)

→ The public key is like a toy that everyone can play with. It has two numbers: the magic number and the big number.
The public key, represented as (e, n), is like a toy that everyone can play with. It consists of two numbers: the public exponent, e, and the big number, n. Just like a toy that can be shared among friends, the public key can be freely distributed to anyone who wants to send encrypted messages. The public exponent, e, serves as a magic number that unlocks the encryption process, while the big number, n, forms the foundation of the encryption algorithm. Together, they enable secure communication between the sender and the recipient, allowing encrypted messages to be exchanged.

?? Encryption: To encrypt a message M, compute C = (M^e) % n

→ Imagine you have a secret message. Put that message inside a special box, raise it to the power of the magic number, and take the remainder when divided by the big number. The result is the encrypted message.
Encryption is like putting a secret message inside a special box and transforming it into an unreadable form. To encrypt a message M, we use a mathematical calculation. We raise the message to the power of the public exponent, e, and then take the remainder when divided by the big number, n. This process of exponentiation and modulo operation transforms the message into a ciphertext, represented by C. It’s like sealing the secret message inside an unbreakable box, ensuring that only the intended recipient with the private key can unlock and read it.

?? Decryption: To decrypt the ciphertext C, compute M = (C^d) % n

→ If you have the encrypted message and the secret numbers, take the encrypted message, raise it to the power of the secret number, and take the remainder when divided by the big number. The result will be the original secret message.
Decryption is like opening the sealed box and revealing the original secret message. To decrypt the ciphertext C, we perform a similar mathematical calculation. We raise the ciphertext to the power of the private exponent, d, and then take the remainder when divided by the big number, n. This process of exponentiation and modulo operation reverses the encryption process, transforming the ciphertext back into the original message, represented by M. It’s like using a special key to unlock the sealed box and retrieve the hidden treasure inside. By using the private key associated with the public key used for encryption, only the intended recipient can decrypt and read the message.

Trace Legacy's description: [HOMELAND: Eversummer, Human Territory
CURRENT AGE: 24
BORN: 457-458

MASS: 160 lbs (73 kg)

Trace Legacy (IPA(key) /treɪs ˈlɛgəsi/) is a male human and the main protagonist of the webcomic Twokinds. He is the leader of the Templar Order.

Appearance
Trace is a pretty average Human in terms of height and build. He has bright light blue eyes and hair, the latter of which he keeps long and messy. He has a triangle tattoo on the left side of his face, also light blue in colour.

Biography
Trace was born into a poor farming family in the village of Eversummer, but was taken in by the Templar at a fairly young age where he quickly developed his magical talents. Whether they where friends prior to Templar training or not is unknown, either way Trace was friends with Red, a fellow student at the Templar Academy. Unlike Trace however, Red showed very little magical potential, which led him to eventually leave the Academy. Trace also meet his future wife Saria while in training too, after a few failed attempts to gain her attention using less practical ways, he managed to work up the nerve to talk to her. They dated for a while and eventually were happily married despite differing personalities. One day, while visiting their house near the borders of the forest, Trace and Saria were attacked by a random Keidran attempting to rob them. Trace managed to deflect one arrow meant for him, but another grazed Saria. Unknown to Trace, the arrow was coated with poison and as the Templar left to chase the thief, she died.
Heartbroken, he tried to use black mana and forbidden magic to resurrect her. It backfired, almost destroying Trace's mind in the process. This incident caused a huge personality change for Trace, he became ruthless and tyrannical as a result of all the suffering he had gone through.
Bent on revenge, he overthrew the old Grand Templar, took her position, and replaced the Master Templars with his own inner group. Afterward, he started a genocidal campaign against the Keidran, transforming the previous peace-keeping force into a military institution to rival the Human's own army. He also started the construction of large mana towers to fulfill some unknown, yet apparently lethal purpose.
While this was happening he found comfort in a relationship with a female bartender called Maren Taverndatter, although he originally did not formed that relationship for love: unbeknownst to everyone he had in mind to use her body as a vessel, that the dark entity Detritus (created by Trace himself) could use to bring Saria's soul back, replacing that of his beloved Saria, but he scrapped the plan for unknown reasons.

Personality
-Trace's personality when he was very young is unknown and his personality is only explained after he had joined the Templar. Lady Nora gives an account that during his younger years in the Templar Order, Trace was rather shy, but also had a bit of a temper.
-After spending a few years with the group and rising to higher positions Trace became more confident, before this he had been discontent with his position, likely due to his natural ability far surpassing that of even more experienced mages. Trace apparently had a slight prejudice against Keidran like many Humans seem to have, though he wasn't outright cruel. Roselyn's flashback recounts that while Trace and Red were still at the Templar Academy together Trace also seemed rather disinterested in such considerations, preferring to study unlike his brash friend.
-When Trace married Saria au Gruhen he seemed to be very content and overjoyed, especially hearing that he was going to be a father soon. As mentioned growing up Trace only had typical Human prejudices towards Keidran.
-However, after the death of both his wife and unborn child at the hands of a Wolf Keidran he grew to completely despise them. After suffering that tragic loss Trace became heartless and bitter, a true tyrant, forcibly taking control or the Templar Order and attempting a mass genocide of Keidran in an act of revenge.

Abilities and Powers
Swordsmanship
Although Trace is much more proficient with magic, he is supposedly also very capable in this regard.

Magic
Trace is a master mage and an expert on magic. In fact, he is considered one of the most powerful Humans alive, even being able to overthrow the then current Grand Templar through combat.
The spells Trace can use are, but not limited to:
A Transformation spell.
Dragonfire, a spell which calls forth mana dragons which explode on impact.
A Summoning Spell that created a large dragon made of Black Mana.
Black Mana tentacles which extend from the back and attacked the opponent. These are resistant to electric attacks.
A Teleportation spell
A Shield Spell
A Healing Spell
A weak Levitation Spell

Trivia
Trace's triangular marking on his cheek is never explained. It may be some kind of magical marking or tattoo as the only other person in the series to have it is Sealeen, another mage albeit a Mercenary.]

Mukuro's description: [RACE: Demon
AGE: 1000+
HEIGHT: 5'2
OCCUPATION: King (despite her being a she)
Mukuro (軀, Mukuro?) is a powerful female demon who lives in Demon World and is part of a triumvirate of Upper S Class demons known as the The Three Kings, who rules over Demon World in the Yu Yu Hakusho series.

Appearance
Mukuro normally conceals her face behind bandages that are studded with paper tag wards (御札 [おふだ], ofuda, translated as Honorable Holy Writing) and around her whole head. Only her damaged right eye is visible through an opening in the bandages and her voice is electronically distorted (and lowered) so as make her sound more like a man to those around her; a charade further reinforced by the fact she uses the supreme-masculine pronoun of "ore" rather than the gender-neutral/feminine pronoun of "watashi" when referring to herself in the Japanese language version.
She also keeps her hands bound and shackled in chains, although it appears the chains have been broken by the time she appears in the series (though not the shackles themselves). She wears loose pale-blue/white pants and black martial arts slippers, a white long-sleeved shirt with a purple vest with gold trim over it, and a long red sash tied around her waist.
However, when she removes the bandages from her face, she has messy orange hair parted to the left with a bandage wrapped around her head (like a headband) and cloth hanging down over much of the right side of her face. Her eye color is blue. Her right eye is in fact covered by a cybernetic lens, although she can see with it perfectly fine without the lens. Furthermore, the entire right side of her body is covered in scar tissue and burn marks: a result of the damage done to her when acid was poured on her. The damage was so extensive that most of her right arm and her right leg have been replaced with mechanical limbs, although the hand (from above the wrist) and foot (from above her ankle) still look natural.

Personality
When Mukuro first appeared, she came off as having a very mysterious personality. During her years as a warrior, few knew that Mukuro was female. It is however, interesting to note that the specific reasoning why she decided to pass herself off as the opposite gender is subject to speculation. In a shocking turnaround, she made a point of removing her bandages at the start of the Demon World Tournament.
Raizen describes Mukuro as a traditionalist and an isolationist and notes that she likes Makai just the way it is and believes it should remain in its pristine, untouched and chaos-ridden state. This said, provided that everyone minds their own business and affairs in their own respective worlds, she will leave both Human and Spirit Worlds as they are as Mukuro focuses her attention solely on Demon World, making Mukuro the lesser of two evils between herself and Yomi, such that should there come a time when Yusuke must extend an alliance to either, Raizen in his final moments advised him to choose the former. While Raizen was slowly starving to death, even stubbornly setting himself as a staunch and primary example for abstaining from human consumption, and Yomi insisting that there is no reason for demons not to hedonistically eat as many humans as they see fit, Mukuro maintained a pragmatic outlook, remarking that the consumption of humans should be limited but not forbidden.
She has been seen engaging in casual conversation with Hiei, and tosses occasional sardonic quips toward him, suggesting she has some sense of humor. In a telling moment, she fully exposed her damaged body to a semi-conscious Hiei and revealed to him her painful past. It is likely that Mukuro gravitated towards Hiei because she saw similarities between herself and him.
In combat, however, Mukuro is completely ruthless. She describes herself as one of the most ruthless, well-known killers that Makai has ever seen. At the same time, Mukuro seems to hate herself as well, punishing herself by wearing chains - largely to represent the emotional damage that holds her in bondage, imprisoned by her own dark past.

History
Mukuro was abandoned on a freezing, snowy night. She was found by a wealthy humanoid demon, who became her "father". He would go on to abuse and rape her at his own leisure. He placed a micro chip in her to show the 'goodness' in him - so that when she ever thought about killing him, the chip would activate and show how good he was to her. In a particular macabre and sadistic twist, he would go on to rape her on her birthdays as a present. As a result, Mukuro came to view everything about her childhood with disgust at both Chikou and herself.
Eventually, at the age of seven, Mukuro poured acid over her head in order to avoid his desire, only leaving her left side unharmed. He tossed her out, which she describes as 'rebirth'. She then replaced her damaged limbs with robotic parts. She swore to seek power at all costs and gained a reputation for violence, covering her face with bandages and leading many to believe that she was a man.

Three Kings Saga
With Yusuke joining Raizen, and Kurama joining Yomi, Mukuro sends a video message (a spirit of words) to Hiei, asking him to come see her. Mukuro asks Hiei to show his true strength by fighting the man that gave him the Jagan eye. The battle ends with both in pieces, and Mukuro revealing that she had Hiei's Hiruseki stone. Then Mukuro places them into regeneration tanks. She puts Hiei's tank into its own room before telling him her life story while removing her clothing to show him her true form.

Powers and Abilities
Mukuro's power depends entirely on her state of mind. In the anime, it seems that her power is directly proportional to how much hatred she feels. As stated by Kirin, Mukuro utilized at most, half of her maximum strength in the Demon World Tournament. Thus, Mukuro at her peak was at least the second most powerful character in the series, with Raizen being the only one capable of being stronger than her.
Mukuro's ruthlessness as a ruler and merciless brutality in battle strike fear in the minds of countless apparitions across the plains of Makai. Her hard-earned reputation alone devastates the composure of her opponents. Many powerful S-Class Demons would rather shamelessly admit defeat than face her in combat. Only when facing Hiei does she hold back and hesitate to go for the win. The similarities of their respective life experiences create a connection between the two, as can be clearly seen in their anime-exclusive battle. This appears to be the source of her hesitation; she finds herself feeling emotions everyone had thought her incapable of feeling given her dark past.
Although Mukuro is primarily a hand-to-hand combatant, she appears in a brief flashback to be using a sword during her time as an assassin, although she is almost never seen carrying one around.

Known Techniques/Moves
Superior S Class Energy: Being a very experienced Upper S Class, her power is only challenged by few Demons. She defeated Hiei, who was an Upper S Class Demon during their battle, despite her using only barely more than half of her full power against him. She also barely defeated Natsume, despite being at a disadvantage due to losing a great part of her rage and hatred, which is the source of her power.
Telepathy: Mukuro appears to hold the power of telepathy, as seen when she accepted Yusuke Urameshi's proposal of a tournament to decide who would rule Demon World, and seemingly sent this thought to Yomi. However, this may also be attributed to Yomi's supposed ability to hear whatever is said within his territory. It is also mentioned by Koenma that, during her battle with Hiei, the two of them were "butting their thoughts against another " as opposed to exchanging any dialogue. This seems to be true, at least in the Japanese subbed version, as they are most definitely communicating, though neither speaks aloud. In the manga, Hiei remarks that "you showed me those memories", referring to Mukuro's past. His choice of "showed" rather than "told about" infers some sort of telepathy between them.
Third Dimensional Cutter (空間切り手, Kūkan Kirite, literally "Space-Cutting Hand"): In the anime, she demonstrates the ability to cut through the entirety of the third dimension. Whatever it comes into contact with will be cut as well. Her control over the location and shape of the cuts makes her utilization of the dimensional distortion considerably more effective than Kuwabara's Jigen-Tou. This is unofficially named in the original Japanese version by Kurama.
Dimensional Forcefield: Enough of these cuts can create an impromptu, and deadly, forcefield that causes severe harm to anything that comes in contact with it. Kurama likened this barrier of Mukuro's to a razor-sharp spider's web.
Energy Punches: She has been seen being able to cause geyser-explosions of energy whenever she punches.
Energy Fist Blast: She can surround her hand in energy and then release it all at once, damaging whatever is in its range. She does this to Hiei in the manga as well, when he coldly insults her affection for him during the Demon World Tournament in the anime and again about her reaction concerning Chikou in the manga, and punches a large hole in his abdomen that blasts him out of her room and fortress-home. It is called "Piercing Beam" in the YuYu Hakusho card game.
Flight: This is a special ability where the user manipulates their Energy so that they can levitate or fly.
Telekinesis: it is highly likely Mukuro possesses telekinetic powers. During her battle with Hiei, Mukuro destroys various large rock formations with her energy, creating several large, sharp stakes of rock. She then uses telekinesis to throw these at Hiei over a significant distance at high speed; however, Hiei is able to destroy them with his sword before damage is dealt. Mukuro's reddish energy can be seen surrounding the rocks, guiding them accurately to their target.

Etymology
The name Mukuro means "body, corpse, tree with rotten core" (軀).

Trivia
In Chapter 161 of the manga, Mukuro is stated to have a Youki of 1,575,000. This would mean she is the most powerful out of all the Three Kings at the time.
Mukuro fought with significantly less power than she was capable of in the Makai Tournament. Her fight with Hiei lessened her anger, and from then on, she was much weaker. This occurred in round three (round two in the anime). In chapter 172 of the manga, one of her underlings goes on to state he was amazed she was able to use more than half of her maximum power, considering the friendly nature of the competition, observing that Mukuro's power varies according to her moods, achieving their highest level when she is at her maddest.
Despite having their abilities shown in the anime, neither Mukuro, Yomi, or Raizen have shown any of their true skills in the manga.]

What is the ethical dilemma in the below case in terms of justice?  
Mr. Lee is a 38‐year‐old construction‐side worker and the sole breadwinner of his family.  He lives in a public housing estate with his wife and two young children. Mrs. Lee received minimal education and had a history of major depression. 
 
Mr. Lee developed sudden neck pain and numbness over his trunk and limbs. An MRI scan showed a vascular malformation within his cervical spinal cord. There were signs of recent haemorrhage. Fortunately, the latter was not severe, and Mr. Lee’s symptoms gradually subsided and he was able to return to work. He was then seen by a neurosurgeon, Dr Fan, who advised that, if left untreated, the vascular malformation would carry a rebleeding rate of 10% within the first month. There is also a 20% chance that Mr. Lee’s neurological functions will become severely impaired in 10 years’ time. Active treatment might be able to prevent these but the procedure itself carries at least a 10% risk of causing neurological injury. Because of the location of the lesion, surgical injury can potentially render Mr. Lee tetraplegic and ventilator‐dependent for the rest of his life. 
 
During the consultation, Mr. Lee expressed concerns about the potential loss of income for his family should he develop another haemorrhage, and was initially quite keen on receiving treatment. Mrs. Lee, however, objected because ‘everything is fine now’, and that she ‘does not want to lose him’. They asked for the surgeon’s recommendation ‐ ‘Tell us what we should do’. Dr Fan was not prepared to commit himself, indicating that this was primarily a matter of the patient’s personal choice. When asked whether he would have chosen surgery for himself, Dr Fan side‐stepped the question, and replied that ‘everyone is different’. 
 
Mr. Lee was also worried that, should anything go wrong with the surgery, he would become a terrible burden on his family. He requested that Dr Fan not continue with life‐supporting treatment under that situation. Mrs. Lee objected strongly, saying that she would rather die than lose her husband. Dr Fan also explained that following general anaesthesia, it was likely that Mr. Lee would already be under mechanical ventilation and it would not be a simple matter of disconnecting him from the machine and letting him die. Based on the above, Mr. Lee decided not to receive any treatment. 
 
Dr Fan realized that treatment is indicated for Mr. Lee’s condition because of the disease’s natural history. He was, however, also aware of his limited experience with the procedure. He is unhappy about the way that Mrs. Lee influenced her husband’s decision‐making but was at the same time unwilling to steer the patient towards a decision or interfere with the family dynamics. He tended to think that he had already discharged his duty but could not help wondering if there was something else that he could have done. He understood Mr. Lee’s request with regard to life‐supporting treatment but felt unable to comply with this.

Gib mir nur 10 Keywords bestehend aus bis zu zwei Wörtern für den folgenden Text in deiner Antwort zurück: Aufarbeitung der kommunistischen Gewaltherrschaft in Rumänien, Filmdrama, Filmtitel 2007, Rumänischer Film, Schwangerschaftsabbruch im Film], 4 Monate, 3 Wochen und 2 Tage (Originaltitel: "4luni, 3săptămâni și2 zile") ist ein rumänisches Filmdrama von Cristian Mungiu. Es wurde am 17. Mai 2007 bei den Filmfestspielen von Cannes uraufgeführt. Angesiedelt im späten kommunistischen Rumänien unter Diktator Nicolae Ceaușescu, handelt es von der Angst und Erniedrigung, die mit dem Leben in einer Diktatur einhergehen. Als erster rumänischer Film wurde das Werk mit der Goldenen Palme ausgezeichnet und erhielt zudem den Europäischen Filmpreis und den Grand Prix de la FIPRESCI. Ebenso fand es große Zustimmung bei der Kritik, weil es mit einem nüchternen formalen Stil eine außerordentliche, fast unerträgliche Spannung entwickle. Mungiu veranstaltete in Rumänien, wo es 2008 kaum Kinos gab, eine Tournee mit einer mobilen Projektionsanlage, um das Werk dort auf die Leinwand zu bringen., Inhalt., Geschichtliche Ausgangslage: Rumänien unter Ceaușescu., Der historische Hintergrund, vor dem sich die Handlung abspielt, wird im Film nicht direkt erläutert. Im kommunistischen Rumänien kam 1965 Nicolae Ceaușescu an die Macht, der sich Moskau nicht unterordnete, das Land auf einen nationalen Sonderweg führte und einen extremen Führerkult pflegte. Die Bespitzelung der Bevölkerung durch den Geheimdienst Securitate war total, die Wirtschaftslage miserabel. Im Unterschied zu anderen mitteleuropäischen Volksrepubliken, in denen sich eine freiheitliche Sexualmoral und Familienpolitik durchsetzte, griff Ceaușescus Ideologie vom nationalen Bevölkerungswachstum mit strengen Vorschriften (Dekret 770) tief ins Privatleben hinein. Verhütungsmittel wurden nicht angeboten, und auf Schwangerschaftsabbruch standen mehrere Jahre Gefängnis. Dennoch wurde er weithin von Laien im Verborgenen unter prekären Bedingungen durchgeführt, was zum Tod von etwa 10.000 Frauen geführt haben soll. Bei unerwarteten Komplikationen kam es vor, dass die Polizei der Frau den Zugang zum Krankenhaus verwehrte, solange sie die Beteiligten nicht nannte. Nach Ceaușescus Sturz 1989 war eine der ersten Gesetzesänderungen die Aufhebung des Abtreibungsverbots., Handlung., Die Filmfachzeitschrift "Positif" gab dem Leser die – in solchen Zeitschriften sonst selten ausgesprochene – Empfehlung, vor dem Kinobesuch nichts über den Film zu lesen. So könne er beim Ansehen des Films denselben Überraschungseffekt erleben wie das Festivalpublikum in Cannes., Eine rumänische Universitätsstadt 1987. Die Studentinnen Găbița und Otilia teilen sich ein Zimmer im Studentenwohnheim, wo ein reger Schwarzhandel mit Kosmetika und Zigaretten stattfindet. Für den Abend haben sie etwas vor, über das sie nicht offen reden. Während Găbița zaudert, treibt Otilia die Vorbereitungen voran. An der Uni leiht sich Otilia noch etwas Geld von ihrem Freund Adi, der darauf besteht, dass sie am Abend zu der Geburtstagsfeier seiner Mutter mitkommt. Sie windet sich, ohne ihren mit Găbița verfolgten Plan offenzulegen, und verspricht dem beharrlichen Adi schließlich, zu kommen. Weil sich eine von Găbița vorgenommene Zimmerreservierung im von ihr vorgesehenen Hotel als gescheitert erweist, muss Otilia in einem anderen Hotel bei der Empfangsdame mühsam ein Zimmer erbetteln. Anschließend holt sie den ihr unbekannten Herrn Bebe ab, mit dem eigentlich Găbița verabredet ist. Diese ist inzwischen im Hotelzimmer eingetroffen, wo sich nun die zentrale Sequenz des Films abspielt., Găbița ist schwanger und will trotz des strengen Verbots abtreiben. Bei der ersten Untersuchung stellt der illegale Abtreibungen vornehmende Bebe fest, dass sie nicht wie behauptet im zweiten, sondern schon im vierten Monat schwanger ist. Die Studentinnen haben weniger Geld dabei, als Bebe erwartet. In einem erpresserischen, erniedrigenden Feilschen erreicht der Mann, dass zusätzlich zur finanziellen Vergütung beide Frauen mit ihm schlafen. Als er sich im Bad aufhält, entdeckt Otilia in seinem Koffer ein Klappmesser und nimmt es an sich. Bebe sterilisiert seine mitgebrachten Utensilien und führt Găbița eine Sonde ein. Bis zur Ausstoßung des Fötus muss sie im Bett liegen bleiben, was zwei Stunden, aber auch zwei Tage dauern könne. Nachdem Bebe gegangen ist, bricht Otilia zur Geburtstagsfeier der Mutter ihres Freundes auf und lässt Găbița allein zurück. Die Rezeptionistin weist sie darauf hin, dass Bebe seinen Ausweis im Hotel vergessen hat. DeGroote's Master of Finance prepares you to navigate financial risk and maximize opportunities in the high-stakes field of finance. The Master of Finance program at DeGroote will not only challenge how you think about finance, but will also help you launch your career in this fast-paced, competitive sector. A career in finance means something different to each of us – let us help you discover what it means to you. The DeGroote MFin Program is a proud partner of the Global Association of Risk Professionals (GARP). While our MFin program is not exclusively a risk management program, our candidate profile, along with a number of our course offerings provide the basis of a strong financial risk management education. According to GARP, each of their partnership institutions “represents the best in financial education around the world.” In only sixteen months, you will be provided with an in-depth training in finance, emphasizing the development of the analytical skills required to address the increasingly complex problems faced by the financial industry. Our program is composed of four terms. Students will complete two four-month academic terms, followed by one four-month scheduled break which provides an opportunity to seek employment, complete external certifications, or develop language skills. Students will return to complete one final four-month academic term in order to complete the program. What you will learn: Essential skills and knowledge in economics, accounting and statistics. How to apply knowledge to core problems in modern finance. Practical experience working with programs such as Python, R., and Matlab. Topics of particular interest and relevance to your anticipated career through elective courses. Key topics of study will be involving : In-depth Evidence-based understanding of Finance, Financial Institutions, Financial Products and Markets founded in Statistics, Economics and Data Analysis ( Capital structure and cost of capital, Capital asset pricing models, Regression analysis, GARCH and stochastic volatility models, Fixed-income securities and their markets, Stock price discovery process and return anomalies, Black-Scholes-Merton option pricing model), and Practical and in-depth understanding of Quantitative Analysis; Advanced Valuation Methodologies and Risk Models (Monte Carlo simulation, Finite difference methods, Forecasting and optimization in finance, Derivatives pricing and hedging strategies, Arbitrage pricing, Fama-French models, APT, Hull-White model, HJM forward rate model, LIBOR market models
Credit risk modeling, Risk budgeting and optimization, Value-at-risk and expected shortfall).

(In the clubroom…)

Natsuki: (already fuming, despite the intense pain in her lower abdomen) “GAH! Yuri still hasn’t arrived yet?! Where is she?!”

Monika: “Calm down, Natsuki. Your anger won’t help a thing.”

Natsuki: (finally calming down) “Fine…I guess I freaked out a little too much. But…this pain is no joke. And I’m only 7 months along in my pregnancy.”

Sayori: (entering the clubroom) “What’s going on?”

Monika: “Natsuki is worried because Yuri hasn’t arrived yet, and she’s also experiencing some intense pain.”

Sayori: “Oh no, Natsuki! Are you okay? Should we call a doctor?”

Natsuki: (holding her belly) “I think I’ll be fine, but Yuri should have been here by now. I hope nothing happened to her.”

Monika: “Don’t worry, Natsuki. Let’s give her a call and check if everything is alright.”

(Sayori takes out her phone and dials Yuri’s number, anxiously waiting for her to pick up.)

Yuri: (over the phone, sounding breathless) “Hello?”

Sayori: “Yuri, where are you? Natsuki is worried, and we’re all waiting for you in the clubroom.”

Yuri: (apologetic) “I am so sorry, guys. I got caught up at the library and lost track of time. I’m on my way now.”

Sayori: “Okay, just make sure to get here safely. Natsuki isn’t feeling well either.”

(Yuri hurriedly hangs up and rushes to the clubroom.)

Natsuki: (relieved) “Finally! What took you so long?”

Yuri: (catching her breath) “I’m really sorry, Natsuki. I didn’t mean to worry you. I lost track of time while researching for a project.”

Monika: “It’s alright, Yuri. Just make sure to inform us if something like this happens again, especially when Natsuki is not feeling well.”

Natsuki: (softening her tone) “Yeah, Yuri. I know you didn’t mean to be late. Just please be more careful next time-” (her pain starts getting more intense) “OWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWW!!!”

Sayori: “Natsuki, are you okay? The pain seems worse now.”

Natsuki: (grimacing) “It’s…getting worse…I th-”

(Suddenly, Natsuki’s water breaks, and she gasps in surprise.)

Monika: “Oh my goodness! Natsuki, your water just broke!”

Yuri: (panicked) “What do we do?! I’ve never been in this situation before!”

Sayori: (trying to stay calm) “Okay, we need to act fast. Natsuki, try to take deep breaths and stay as calm as possible.”

Natsuki: (gritting her teeth) “Sayori…I don’t think I can…I feel like I need to push.”

Monika: “It’s okay, Natsuki. We’re here for you. Just do your best to breathe and try not to panic.”

Yuri: (nervously) “Should we call for an ambulance? We might need professional help.”

Natsuki: (struggling) “No time, Yuri…the contractions are too close together…”

Sayori: “Okay, Yuri, help me quickly prepare a clean area for Natsuki to deliver the baby. We’ll need towels and warm water.”

Yuri: “Right, I’ll go grab some towels and fill a basin with warm water.”

Monika: “Natsuki, just keep breathing and pushing when you feel the urge. We’ll support you through this.”

(Natsuki continues to endure the intense pain and tries her best to push during each contraction. Yuri and Sayori quickly bring towels and a basin of warm water to the clubroom.)

Yuri: “Here, Natsuki. We’ve prepared a clean area for you.”

Sayori: “Natsuki, we’re here for you. You can do this.”

Monika: “Remember to breathe, Natsuki. Just a little more and we’ll see your baby.”

(Just then, Natsuki lets out a guttural scream - a sign that her baby was on its way out.)

Backenzahn (der sogenannte Weisheitszahn) vorhanden, das Dentin aber nur an wenigen Stellen freigelegt ist, wird das Lebensalter beim Eintritt des Todes auf ca. 20 bis 30 Jahre geschätzt.', 'Schoetensack schloss aus der Ähnlichkeit des Gebisses auf die Verwandtschaft zum Menschen der Gegenwart ("Homo sapiens") und stellte den Unterkiefer daher zur Gattung "Homo" – eine Sichtweise, die auch heute noch einhellig von den Paläoanthropologen vertreten wird. Aus dem Umstand, dass dem Unterkiefer – im Unterschied zum modernen Menschen – unter anderem das Kinn fehlt, leitete Schoetensack die Berechtigung ab, eine neue Art mit dem Art-Epitheton "heidelbergensis" zu definieren. Durch den Untertitel seiner Erstbeschreibung – „Ein Beitrag zur Paläontologie des Menschen“ – bezog Schoetensack zugleich auf Seiten des Darwinismus „eindeutig Position in der großen Auseinandersetzung seiner Zeit über die Entstehung des Menschen: nämlich dass der Mensch sich aus dem Tierreich heraus entwickelt hat und nicht bereits als fertiges Wesen einem biblischen Schöpfungsakt zu verdanken sei.“', 'Über die genaue Position des Unterkiefers von Mauer in der Ahnenkette des modernen Menschen äußerte sich Schoetensack nur vorsichtig: Er schrieb in seiner Studie zurückhaltend, dass es „möglich erscheint, daß der Homo Heidelbergensis der Vorfahrenreihe des europäischen Menschen“ angehöre und – nach eingehenden Vergleichen mit anderen europäischen Fossilien – an anderer Stelle gleichermaßen vage: „Wir müssen daher die Mandibula des Homo Heidelbergensis als präneandertaloid bezeichnen.“ Die Einordnung des Unterkiefers von Mauer in die Zeit vor den Neandertalern erwies sich als zutreffend.', 'Falsch lag Schoetensack – wie viele seiner Fachkollegen um die Wende zum 20. Jahrhundert – allerdings mit der Abschätzung der verwandtschaftlichen Nähe des Unterkiefers von Mauer mit den Menschenaffen (Hominiden): „Die Mandibula des Homo Heidelbergensis läßt den Urzustand erkennen, welcher dem gemeinsamen Vorfahren der Menschheit und der Menschenaffen zukam.“ 1924 wurde im heutigen Südafrika das bis dahin älteste Fossil aus dem Formenkreis der Hominiden entdeckt – das Kind von Taung – das rund zwei Millionen Jahre älter ist als der Unterkiefer von Mauer und trotz seines hohen Alters nicht an der gemeinsamen Basis von Menschen und Menschenaffen steht.', 'Datierung.', 'Otto Schoetensack ließ die Fundstelle am Boden der Sandgrube mit einem Gedenkstein markieren, auf dem eine horizontale Linie das Fundniveau darstellte. Ob sein Wunsch erfüllt wurde, dieser Stein möge liegen bleiben, auch wenn die Sandgrube dereinst wieder verfüllt werde, ist unbekannt; tatsächlich wurde jener Teil der Grube, in dem der Unterkiefer zutage trat, in den 1930er-Jahren mit Abraum verfüllt, anschließend als Ackerland renaturiert und 1982 zum Naturschutzgebiet erklärt; die Fundstelle ist daher der Forschung nicht mehr zugänglich. Eine absolute Datierung der Fundstelle mit Hilfe moderner wissenschaftlicher Verfahren war daher bislang unmöglich. Ersatzweise wurde wiederholt versucht, mit Hilfe stratigrafischer Methoden das Alter des Fossils zumindest einzugrenzen.', 'Die nur zehn Zentimeter dicke Fundschicht war bereits von Schoetensack als „Geröllschicht, durch kohlensauren Kalk etwas verkittet, mit ganz dünnen Lagen von Letten, der mit HCl schwach braust“, beschrieben worden. Über und unter der Fundschicht lagerten Sand in diversen abgrenzbaren Schichten und anderes Material, das sich im Verlauf von Jahrtausenden am Rande eines früheren Neckar-Bogens abgelagert hatte. Im Vorwort seiner Studie heißt es: „Das Alter dieser Sande wird nach den darin angetroffenen Säugetierresten gemeinhin als altdiluvial angegeben; einige darin vertretene Arten lassen aber auch deutliche Beziehungen zu den jüngsten Abschnitten des Tertiärs, dem Pliozän, erkennen.“ Nach heutiger Datierung würden diese Angaben eine untere Altersgrenze von rund 780.000 Jahren und eine obere von mehreren Millionen Jahren bedeuten.', 'Obwohl Schoetensack ausführlich zahlreiche fossile Tierarten beschreibt, deren Überreste in der Sandgrube gefunden wurden, hat er offenbar nicht versucht, gezielt die von ihm als „Schicht 4“ bezeichnete Fundschicht des Unterkiefers nach Fossilien zu durchsuchen. Stattdessen führt er in seiner Schrift seitenweise Funde an, deren Zuordnung zu bestimmten Fundschichten ihm offenbar nicht möglich ist. Eine relative Datierung anhand von Begleitfunden ist daher anhand des von ihm vorgestellten Materials nicht möglich.', 'In der 2007 zum 100. import pandas as pd

input_files = []
while True:
    file = input("Enter the name of an input file (or ‘done’ to finish): ")
    if file.lower() == ‘done’:
        break
    input_files.append(file)

# Create an empty dataframe to store merged data
merged_df = pd.DataFrame()

# Read and merge the input files
for file in input_files:
    df = pd.read_excel(file)
    df[‘Date’] = file
    merged_df = pd.concat([merged_df, df])

# Write the merged dataframe to an output Excel file
output_file = ‘merged_data.xlsx’
merged_df.to_excel(output_file, index=False)

print(“Merged dataframe has been written to”, output_file)

Gib mir nur 10 Keywords bestehend aus bis zu zwei Wörtern für den folgenden Text in deiner Antwort zurück: [['Britische Geschichte (Zwischenkriegszeit)', 'Conservative Party', 'Politik 1922', 'Politikgeschichte (Vereinigtes Königreich)'], 'Das Carlton-Club-Treffen von 1922 war ein Treffen der Parlamentsabgeordneten der britischen Conservative Party (Konservative Partei) am 19. Oktober 1922. Es fand im namensgebenden Carlton Club statt. Anlass war eine offene Diskussion um die Frage, ob die Partei die Koalitionsregierung mit dem von David Lloyd George geführten Teil der Liberal Party (Liberale Partei) über die nächste Unterhauswahl hinaus fortsetzen oder beenden solle. Während die Parteiführung um Austen Chamberlain für eine Fortführung der Koalition eintrat, machte sich eine Hinterbänkler-Gruppe um Andrew Bonar Law und Stanley Baldwin dafür stark, die anstehende Unterhauswahl als unabhängige Kraft zu führen. Die Hinterbänkler konnten sich durchsetzen und erzwangen so ein Ende der Koalition. Lloyd George trat daraufhin als Premierminister zurück, die Konservativen dagegen bildeten eine Regierung unter ihrem neuen Vorsitzenden Bonar Law.', 'Das Treffen hatte weitreichende Auswirkungen. Lloyd George, der die letzten Jahre die politische Bühne Großbritanniens dominiert hatte, hielt nie wieder ein politisches Amt. Eine mögliche Spaltung der Konservativen wurde dagegen ebenso verhindert wie die von Lloyd George, Lord Birkenhead und Winston Churchill betriebene Fusion aus moderaten Konservativen und Liberalen zu einer neuen Zentrumspartei. In der britischen Parteienlandschaft, in der sich aufgrund des Mehrheitswahlrechts traditionell zwei Parteien als Antipoden gegenüberstehen, bildete sich für die nächsten Jahre ein unbeständiges Dreiparteiensystem heraus, bestehend aus Konservativen, Liberalen und der Labour Party (Arbeiterpartei), wobei die Liberalen in dieser Phase als Gegenspieler der Konservativen schrittweise von der aufstrebenden Labour-Partei abgelöst wurden.', 'Das Carlton-Club-Treffen ist auch in der heutigen politischen Berichterstattung britischer Medien präsent und wird regelmäßig zitiert, um die Macht der konservativen Hinterbänkler herauszustreichen.', 'Hintergrund.', 'Seit ihrer klaren Niederlage bei der Unterhauswahl von 1906 hatte sich die Konservative Partei in jahrelanger Opposition befunden. Die sozialen Reformgesetze der regierenden Liberalen, die maßgeblich von Premierminister H. H. Asquith und seinem Schatzkanzler David Lloyd George vorangetrieben wurden, trafen auf den heftigen Widerstand der Konservativen. Vor allem das sogenannte „Volksbudget“ (ein Gesetzespaket mit umfangreichen Steuern auf Landeigentümer, um soziale Maßnahmen zu finanzieren), der nachfolgende Parliament Act 1911, der das Veto-Recht des konservativ dominierten Oberhauses (House of Lords) radikal beschnitt und die andauernde Home-Rule-Frage über die irische Selbstverwaltung sorgten für erbitterte Auseinandersetzungen. Die Konservativen vertraten die Interessen der Landbesitzer und definierten sich traditionell als entschiedene Gegner der irischen Selbstverwaltung – so nannten sie sich auch, um dies auszudrücken, ab 1912 offiziell die „Conservative and Unionist Party“. Die erbitterten Konflikte um das Veto-Recht des Oberhauses hatten schließlich auch zu innerparteilichen Verwerfungen der Konservativen geführt; eine Gruppe um Lord Halsbury forderte (erfolglos) eine totale Opposition um jeden Preis. Dieser rechte Flügel wurde wegen seiner kompromisslosen Haltung als „Ditchers“ oder auch als „Die-hards“ (abgeleitet aus der englischen Redewendung "die in the last ditch", deutsch etwa "Kampf bis zum bitteren Ende") bezeichnet. Die Halsbury-Gruppe konnte die Verabschiedung des Parliament Act nicht verhindern, agitierte jedoch erfolgreich gegen den aus ihrer Sicht allzu zögerlichen Parteiführer Arthur Balfour, der im November 1911 zurücktrat. Sein Nachfolger wurde Andrew Bonar Law.', 'Der Beginn des Ersten Weltkriegs im August 1914 hatte zunächst zu einem Stillhalteabkommen in der Parteipolitik geführt, um nationale Einigkeit zu demonstrieren. Die Konservativen selbst bezeichneten dies als „patriotische Opposition“. Angesichts sich mehrender militärischer Niederlagen und wiederholter Rückschläge war dieses Abkommen jedoch zunehmend an seine Grenzen gestoßen. Vor allem die von Winston Churchill unnachgiebig betriebene „Dardanellenstrategie“ mit dem Ziel, das Osmanische Reich aus dem Krieg zu drängen und damit einen sicheren Seeweg zum Verbündeten Russland zu schaffen, war umstritten; die daraus resultierende fatale und verlustreiche Schlacht von Gallipoli hatte zu heftigen Auseinandersetzungen und schließlich zum Rücktritt des Ersten Seelords John Arbuthnot Fisher geführt. Dies und die sogenannte Munitionskrise von 1915 (ein Mangel an Artilleriegeschossen bei den britischen Truppen an der Westfront) sorgte auch für heftige Kritik der britischen Presse. Eine weitere Alleinregierung der Liberalen und ein Stillhalten der konservativen Opposition war unter diesen Umständen zunehmend unmöglich geworden. Deshalb wurde 1915 eine Koalition zwischen den von Premierminister Asquith geführten Liberalen und den Konservativen um ihren Parteiführer Andrew Bonar Law gebildet. Dazu wurde diese Regierung von Teilen der Labour-Partei unterstützt – obwohl Teile der Labour-Partei der Regierung fernblieben, da sie nicht ihre pazifistische Überzeugung verraten wollten.', 'Während die führenden Mitglieder der Konservativen bei der Regierungsbildung bereitwillig eigene Ambitionen zurückstellten und sich im Interesse der Sache in mehreren Fällen auch mit niederen Posten zufrieden gaben, zeigten viele Mitglieder in der Basis der Partei großen Ehrgeiz, woraus ein scharfer Wettbewerb um die wenigen zur Verfügung stehenden Posten resultierte. So wurde Bonar Law, der sich trotz seiner Rolle als konservativer Parteiführer mit dem Posten des Kolonialministers zufrieden gegeben hatte, mit Briefen geradezu bombardiert, in denen ehrgeizige Anhänger um ein subalternes Amt baten.', 'Bis Ende 1916 war auch Premierminister Asquith ins Zentrum der Kritik gerückt; Asquith, der die Presse verachtete, lehnte es ab, sich mit ihr abzugeben und für seine Sache zu werben. Der mächtige Zeitungsmagnat Lord Northcliffe, Eigentümer von "The Times" und "Daily Mail", arbeitete dagegen auf seine Absetzung hin. In der Presse wurde Asquith einerseits wegen seiner exaltierten Frau Margot (die einen Teil ihrer Schulzeit in Berlin verbracht hatte und auch im Krieg noch offen germanophil war), andererseits wegen seiner bekannt abwartenden Strategie, die er vormals selbst mit den Worten „Wait and see“ (Abwarten und schauen) beschrieben hatte, harsch kritisiert. Asquiths politische Gegner, zu denen Edward Carson und Alfred Milner zählten, warfen ihm Entscheidungsschwäche und Indifferenz vor; dies, andauernde langwierige Diskussionen und zahlreiche interne Intrigen machten einen schnellen Entscheidungsprozess im Kabinett unmöglich. Dagegen erwarb sich Lloyd George als Munitions- und nachfolgend als Kriegsminister eine Reputation für energisches und tatkräftiges Handeln. Mitte November 1916 fanden sich Carson, Lloyd George und Bonar Law zusammen und forcierten in der Folge eine Petition: Ein kleineres Kriegskabinett, bestehend aus vier Personen mit Lloyd George an der Spitze, sollte gebildet werden, Asquith diesem dagegen nicht angehören.', 'Asquith weigerte sich, dies zu akzeptieren, woraufhin Lloyd George seinen Rücktritt einreichte. Da Bonar Law jedoch Lloyd George unterstützte und den Rücktritt aller konservativen Minister androhte, sah Asquith keine andere gangbare Option mehr und trat von seinem Amt zurück. Diese Entscheidung führte zur Spaltung der Liberalen Partei. Während der als Premierminister verdrängte Asquith mit seinen Anhängern in die Opposition ging, verblieb ein (kleinerer) Teil der Liberalen unter dem neuen Premierminister Lloyd George in der Koalition.', 'Die „Coupon-Wahl“ 1918.', 'Diese Koalition gewann die Britische Unterhauswahl 1918, bei der erstmals allen Männern über 21 Jahren und Frauen über 30 Jahren das Wahlrecht gewährt worden war. Diese Wahl wird auch als „Coupon-Wahl“ bezeichnet – da die Regierung zuvor Schreiben (coupons) an bestimmte Politiker der Liberalen und Konservativen gesandt hatte, die sie als Anhänger der bestehenden Koalition auswies. Dies verschärfte die bereits bestehende interne Spaltung der Liberalen Partei und versetzte ihr einen schweren Schlag. Die Koalitionsregierung gewann bei der Wahl eine deutliche Mehrheit mit den Konservativen als Hauptgewinner, die Liberalen unter Asquith schrumpften dagegen zu einer Rumpfpartei. Auch die Koalitionsliberalen befanden sich nun deutlich in der Minderheit; die Koalition bestand zu drei Vierteln aus Konservativen und einem Viertel aus Liberalen auf der Seite Lloyd Georges, während Asquiths Liberale von der aufstrebenden Labour-Partei als die führende Oppositionspartei abgelöst worden waren. Diese hatte nach Beendigung des Krieges ebenfalls die Koalition verlassen. In Irland gewann die radikale Partei Sinn Féin, die für die Loslösung Irlands aus dem Vereinigten Königreich eintrat und keine Abgeordneten nach Westminster entsandte, auf Kosten der moderaten Irish Parliamentary Party erstmals 73 Sitze. Die Irish Parliamentary Party, die seit vielen Jahren im Unterhaus mit den Liberalen alliiert war, wurde bei der Wahl nahezu ausgelöscht.', 'Die schwierige Lage der Liberalen hatte sich auch durch die fällige Neuaufteilung der Wahlkreise verschärft, die der neuen Bevölkerungsverteilung Rechnung trug. Zahlreiche Sitze, in denen die Liberalen traditionell gewonnen hatten, waren aufgelöst und dafür mehrere neue Sitze mit einer konservativen Mehrheit kreiert worden. Im Ganzen stieg die Zahl der Abgeordneten im Unterhaus um 37 an; die neue Aufteilung gab den Konservativen dabei in den Landesteilen England, Schottland und Wales insgesamt 28 neue Sitze im Unterhaus verglichen mit der letzten Unterhauswahl im Dezember 1910, während Liberale und Labour gemeinsam auf nur insgesamt 8 neue Sitze kamen.', 'Das neue Parlament unterschied sich jedoch nicht nur in seiner relativen Parteienstärke erheblich von seinem Vorgänger, auch die personelle Zusammensetzung der Parteien – insbesondere auch der Konservativen – hatte sich substantiell verändert. Stark vertreten in der konservativen Unterhausfraktion waren nun Geschäftsleute, die ihren Wohlstand oftmals auch dem Krieg verdankten. Der konservative Politiker J. C. C. Davidson, Privatsekretär Bonar Laws und 1920 bei einer Nachwahl ins Unterhaus gewählt, schilderte Lord Stamfordham, dem Sekretär von König Georg V., dass der altmodische Gentleman vom Land und die akademischen Berufe kaum noch repräsentiert seien, dafür jedoch ein hoher Anteil an profitgierigen, nüchternen Männern nun die Reihen der konservativen Partei aufgefüllt hätte. Auch Lloyd George äußerte bei einer Gelegenheit, er habe das Gefühl, nicht mehr zum Unterhaus zu sprechen, sondern zu einer Handelskammer auf der einen und zum Trades Union Congress auf der anderen Seite. 雅思作文评分：The diagram illustrates the steps in the process of regenerating plastic bottles.
Overall, we can see that this process includes 9 steps and the plastic bottles can be repeatly recycled.
At the beginning of the process, people throw the bottles into the bin which collects recyclable bottles. After that, a truck will collect and bring them to the recycling centre. Bottles in the centre will be sorted by workers, the unrecyclable part will be abandoned. The recyclable part will be compressed into blocks in the following step. Then a crushing machine will completely grind the blocks, the grains will be washed and be putted into a machine that produce plastic pellets. Before the pellets becomes raw material, they will be heated. Some raw materials can be producted as bottles and lunch boxes, the others can be made into clothes, pens, or recyclable plastic bags. Once they are throwed into the bin, they will start a new circulation.

He stares down at a large cavern, where a strange sight catches his eye - five different girls, unlike any Amatsumagatsuchi has seen. He descends upon the girls, and sees that each girl’s clothes resemble a different type of monster that inhabits the Minecraft world - the Skeleton, the Creeper, the Cave Spider, the Enderman, and the Blaze. (Just then, Sayori and MC arrive.)

Story prompt: John had a love for history and storytelling, and it was no surprise that he mixed both together to create his historical fiction stories. John was also not a fan of adding sci-fi or fantasy and magic to these stories, as he found them unnecessary and detracting from the point. Today on August 28, 2023, John stumbled across some articles on archaeology. One article caught his attention, its headline reading, "Archaeologists find 3,000-year-old priest’s tomb in Peru". John was interested and read the rest of the article, "Cajamarca, Peru — Archaeologists in northern Peru have unearthed a 3,000-year-old tomb which they believe might have honored an elite religious leader in the Andean country some three millennia ago. Dubbed the “Priest of Pacopampa,” referring to the highland archaeological zone where the tomb was found, the priest was buried under six layers of ash mixed with black earth, with decorated ceramic bowls and seals indicating ancient ritual body paint used for people of elite standing, Peru’s culture ministry said in a statement on Saturday. Two seals were also found along the upper edges of the tomb, one with an anthropomorphic face looking east and another with a jaguar design facing west." John read the rest of the article, "Project leader Yuji Seki said the large size of the tomb, nearly two meters (2.2 yards) in diameter and one meter (3.3 feet) deep, was “very peculiar,” as was the position of the body lying face down with one half of his body extended and feet crossed.The body was also found with a bone shaped into a tupu, a large pin used by Andean Amerindians to hold cloaks and ponchos, which would have been used to hold a woman’s blanket, he added. “Though this person is a man, the associations are very peculiar,” said Seki. “I think this was a leader in his time.”" Using both the facts and details found in this article and his imagination to fill in the gaps, John began to write his story.

按照 概论、洞察、创意张力、执行、总结，这五个步骤，以简洁的方式写出以下内容案列分析。
标题：佳能打印机拼贴广告，转场丝滑又出人意料

在这个万物皆可线上操作的时代，我们还需要什么？
近期，佳能为打印机产品发布一支创意广告，在情景巧思中传递：创造美的同时，更要让美丽被看到。
美丽值得被看到
短片涵盖了能想象到的应用场景，比如文字创作、日常办公；
也有不那么常见、以及很容易被忽视的时刻，比如孩子打印自己的画作、准爸妈打印彩超图像、 厨师打印出精心设计的最新菜单、妈妈送孩子上学前也没忘带上文件，真家庭工作两不误......
佳能将这些都视为“创造美丽”的过程，也回到创作者视角告诉更多人，具体操作时并不是一帆风顺：
创意也幽默地一笔带过打工人周五加班、一个设计被所有人包围，这些熟悉的场景。
而在情境内容之外，短片也用不同的创意手法，改变大家对于打印机广告的固有印象。

write 7 headings related to this content - Introducing Pointzap – Revolutionizing Customer Retention and Allegiance Programs
Customer retention and allegiance programs are very important for businesses in today’s competitive market. However, Traditional Programs often fail to provide meaningful benefits and engage with customers effectively. This is where Pointzap comes in offering unique solutions to address these challenges as well as maximize the value of allegiance points. 
Pointzap leverages blockchain technology to ensure safe, secure and transparent transactions.  Unlike Traditional programs, Pointzap aggregates allegiance points from various sources such as retail stores, flight booking, insurance companies, gas stations etc. Instead of letting these points go to waste, Pointzap allows customers to exchange them for digital assets, products, and services.
Seamless Hassle-Free Experience
Pointzap operates on a unified app/platform, making the process seamless and hassle-free for users. Customers can transfer their off-chain allegiance points onto the blockchain and transform them into digital assets. By collecting and swapping points from different users, Pointzap increases their values by providing users with more valuable and versatile allegiance currency. In addition, customers can swap their allegiance points for ZAP, a notice token for the Pointzap platform. By staking ZAP, users can earn extra rewards such as gift cards, which encourage them to engage actively within the platform.  
Pointzap Promoting Customer Engagement and Trustworthiness
Pointzap not only increases customer engagement and retention but also promotes brand trustworthiness. By offering a secure and transparent program experience businesses can increase their stronger relationships with their clients. In this way, customers can feel more confident while interacting with your brand.
Benefits of using Pointzap
Pointzap offers various benefits to both businesses and customers.
•	Earn Pointzap Tokens – You can make online purchases from hundreds of e-commerce and travel websites and earn Pointzap tokens enhancing loyalty rewards.
•	Flexible Currency Conversion – You can also convert your Pointzap tokens into other cryptocurrencies, allowing you to manage your assets properly.
•	Effortless Assets Management – You can consolidate all your digital assets including reward points, miles, cryptocurrencies, gift cards and NFTs into one decentralized platform. 
•	Exchange Rewards and Cryptocurrencies – You can also convert various cryptocurrencies and rewards into Pointzap tokens and enjoy bonus allocation prior to the ICO.
•	Stake for attractive returns – You can stake Pointzap currency and unlock attractive returns such as free offers and discounts across various products and services.
Avail Unprecedented Redemption Opportunities
With Pointzap the possibilities of redeeming your tokens are limitless.
•	Over 900 Flights 
•	Over 700000 Hotels 
•	Over 75000 Tour Attractions 
•	Global Events and Experience Tickets
•	Access to Premium clubs and entertainment venues
•	Discount on Lifestyle subscriptions
•	NFTs and Gaming currencies
•	Cryptocurrencies
Pointzap is a groundbreaking platform that takes customers’ allegiance programs to the next level. By leveraging Blockchain Technology Pointzap empowers businesses to create innovative programs that drive trust, engagement and long-term loyalty. 
Embrace Pointzap today and unlock the full potential of the allegiance program. 
FAQs
What is Pointzap?
A Pointzap is a platform that revolutionizes the customer engagement program by leveraging blockchain technology. It allows seamless exchange as well as utilization of allegiance points as tradeable digital assets offering a customer more valuable and versatile allegiance currency.
How does Pointzap work for businesses?
Pointzap operates on a unified app platform which makes it a seamless hassle-free experience. It can transform your off-chain allegiance points onto the blockchain and transforms them into trading assets. In addition, it also offers the option to swap allegiance points for ZAP, the native token of the platform and you can earn additional rewards through staking. 
How can I earn Pointzap tokens?
You can earn Pointzap tokens by making online purchases from hundreds of e-commerce and travel websites. Pointzap rewards your loyalty by offering tokens for qualifying transactions as well.
What can I do with Pointzap tokens?
Pointzap tokens offer various benefits. You can exchange them for a wide range of products and services including flights, hotels, global events, NFTs, gaming currencies and other cryptocurrencies. 
How can I Participate in Pointzap ICO?
Pointzap offers bonus allocation ahead of its ICO (Initial Coin Offerings). You can participate by exchanging your rewards as well as cryptocurrencies for Pointzap tokens, ensuring you enjoy the benefit of early involvement.

# syntax=docker/dockerfile:experimental
FROM python:3.9.17

ENV LANG C.UTF-8

USER root
ARG HOME=/root

ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
RUN apt update \
    && apt install --assume-yes \
        gcc \
        ffmpeg \
        libsm6 \
        libxext6 \
        git \
        curl
ARG RCLONE_INCLUDE="no"
ENV RCLONE_INCLUDE=${RCLONE_INCLUDE}
ARG RCLONE_VERSION="1.55.1"
ENV RCLONE_VERSION=${RCLONE_VERSION}
RUN [ "${RCLONE_INCLUDE}" != "yes" ] \
    || \
    ( \
        curl -Of https://downloads.rclone.org/v${RCLONE_VERSION}/rclone-v${RCLONE_VERSION}-linux-amd64.zip \
        && unzip -a "rclone-v${RCLONE_VERSION}-linux-amd64.zip" \
        && cp "rclone-v${RCLONE_VERSION}-linux-amd64/rclone" /usr/bin/rclone.new \
        && chmod 755 /usr/bin/rclone.new \
        && chown root:root /usr/bin/rclone.new \
        && mv /usr/bin/rclone.new /usr/bin/rclone \
        && rm -r "rclone-v${RCLONE_VERSION}-linux-amd64" \
    )

ENTRYPOINT [ "bash", "bootstrap/bin", "poetry", "run", "python", "-m", "app.main" ]

В британских географических названиях можно найти отражение всех исторических этапов Великобритании, начиная с заселения островов кельтами. Определить происхождение топонима можно по его характерным чертам и окончаниям.
С 9 века до нашей эры на Британские острова вторглись кельтские племена. К 1 веку до нашей эры они смешались с местным населением и образовали народ под названием бритты. Кельтские названия многих природных элементов – рек, холмов, урочищ – сохранились до наших времен. Реки Avon и Thames имеют кельтское происхождение, также как менее известные Don, Derwent, Dee, Severn.

Кельтские названия населенных пунктов менее распространены, но все же сохранились. Особенно заметно кельтское наследие в топонимике Шотландии, Уэльса, Ирландии и Корнуолла – территориях, где кельтские языки использовались гораздо дольше и используются до сих пор.

Варианты ответа:
 Дейтаграммы собираются сразу же после прохождения сети с маленьким МЕП, так как некоторые сети, проходимые после места фрагментации, имеют большое значение МЕП, и будет неэффективно, если их будут пересекать только маленькие фрагменты

Catwoman se palpe les grandes lèvres et les petites lèvres pour vérifier, mais constate qu’elle va bien. Mais Batman est saisit d’une intense douleur, est plié en deux, a du mal a respirer et parler, et sent qu’il va vomir. Batman, entrain de se masser les parties douloureuses voit Catwoman entrain de se palper le même endroit, mais sans éprouver de douleur. Batman ne comprend pas pourquoi les choses sont si différentes, alors Catwoman le lui explique, de manière moqueuse et un peut familière, en profite de l’avantage qu’elle viens d’obtenir dans leur affrontement pour lui infliger une petite humiliation.
Catwoman sourit taquinement à Batman et lui explique que les organes sexuels masculins sont situés à l’extérieur de leur corps et donc plus vulnérables aux blessures, tandis que les organes sexuels féminins sont situés à l’intérieur et mieux protégés. Elle ajoute avec un sourire narquois que c’est pour cela que les hommes doivent être plus prudents et protéger leurs parties intimes lorsqu’ils se battent. Batman, agacé par l’humiliation de Catwoman, se relève et reprend son sérieux. Batman, encore affaiblis par ses membres douloureux va alors pour reprendre le combat, mais il n’a même pas le temps de porter le moindre coup contre Catwoman car dans sa charge maladroite il n’a pas vu la borne incendie sur son chemin qu’il percute de plein fouet, se prenant par là même un nouveau coup dans l’entre jambes. il se retrouve a nouveau a terre entrain de gémir, grimacer, transpirer, le souffle court sans pouvoir parler.
